<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n41023d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41023d">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41023d"> 23(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> condone</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><i>Absolute bars</i> <font color="green">[binding the Court to dismiss a Petition]</font> are three in number, namely:&mdash;connivance, <mark>condonation</mark> and collusion. &hellip; <i>Condonation</i> is &ldquo;complete forgiveness of the conjugal offence with full knowledge of all the circumstances&rdquo;. <small> Maud I. Crofts, <a name="MICW" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#MICW"><cite title="source">Women under English Law</cite></a>, 1st ed. (1925) 24</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
